714839f-a.title: Manhattan: 93rd Street - 5th Avenue
714839f-a.text:
East 93rd Street, at, adjoining and east of the S.E. corner of Fifth
Ave (background to foreground). The private houses bear Nos. 4, 6 and 8
while the apartment house at the corner is No. 1116 Fifth Ave. Note a
portion of Central Park in the background.
June 22, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

723557f-c.title: Manhattan: Avenue B - 93rd Street (East)
723557f-c.text:
(1)
Tompkins Square: A northeastward view across the northeasterly
corner of same, showing the wading pool in the central-easterly half.
Buildings shown face on the east side of Ave. B, north from East
9th (right) to 10th (left) Streets, prominent of which is the
Christodoro House at the N.E. corner of the first two points.
August 31, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
(2 A. 3)
A aet of 2 views of the same pool. No. E is due east to Ave. B at
East 8th Street and showing St. Brigids Roman Catholic Church at the
S.E. corner of Mame. No. 3 is in the opposite direction, westward to
Ave. A.
July 24, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
